\chapter{Process Simulation and Modelling}

The SMR-CCS process was simulated in DWSIM using the Peng-Robinson
thermodynamic package. The flowsheet comprises the steam reformer, a
water-gas shift reactor, a gas-liquid separator for water removal, and a
PSA unit for \chem{H_2} recovery. The \chem{CO_2}-rich tail gas is routed
to a cooler-flash separator and a component splitter for \chem{CO_2}
separation, followed by a multi-stage compression train for storage.

\chapter{Industrial Analogue}

This flowsheet mirrors Air Liquide's CRYOCAP\textsuperscript{TM}~H\textsubscript{2}
technology, in commercial operation at Port-Jérôme, France since 2015,
capturing 100{,}000~t/yr of \chem{CO_2} at over 97\% capture rate
\cite{AirLiquide2015,Antonini2020}. The cooler-flash separator and component
splitter in this simulation correspond to its cryogenic purification and
PSA/membrane stages (TRL~9). Linde's HISORP~CC is a parallel commercial
alternative \cite{Linde2021}.


